{"TopicId":140808,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Which mod can pause an airplane in atmosphere?","CreatedByName":"Ser","CreatedById":104207,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-30T09:46:08Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Ser","CreatedById":104207,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-30T09:46:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know there was such a mod for 1.0.5 but now I can\u0027t find any traces of it and completely forgot its name. Is it still alive?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy do I need that mod: often I have to perform long atmospheric flights to complete surface survey contracts on the opposite side of Kerbin and after 2.5 hours of flight when only 50km is left to the waypoint, KAC says \u0022Tada! Your satellite nears Apoapsis and needs to be babysitted. Switch or die\u0022. So it would be quite neat to pause the plane where it is, switch to the satellite and then get back to the point where I\u0027ve left.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Acvila","CreatedById":155891,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-30T11:33:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ntry this\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/62946-025-time-control-92314-v132/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;embedComment=2557201\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0026amp;page=11#comment-2557201\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ser","CreatedById":104207,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-30T13:26:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222607846\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140808\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464607998\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155891\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Acvila\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Acvila said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ntry this\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/62946-025-time-control-92314-v132/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;embedComment=2557201\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0026amp;page=11#comment-2557201\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre you sure? Neither the description nor the video shows that this mod can freeze an aircraft mid-flight and let you switch to space center and back.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-30T13:27:15Z\u0022 title=\u002205/30/2016 01:27  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 30, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Ser\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drew Kerman","CreatedById":103177,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-30T14:04:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit was air park\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/123669-104-airpark/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurrently abandoned but has been integrated into Hooligan Labs airship mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor now though, you can do some SFS file merging if you want. You can now save a flight while in atmosphere so just quicksave and then switch to your probe. Take care of that, and then when you go back to the space center make a copy of your SFS file. Now quickload back to the plane and finish that mission. Now after you\u0027re back at the space center exit to the main menu (or quit the game) and then copy the VESSEL{} data for your probe over the node in your main SFS file. Now everything is all synced up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr schedule things better \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-30T14:08:10Z\u0022 title=\u002205/30/2016 02:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 30, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Gaiiden\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ser","CreatedById":104207,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-30T14:38:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222607964\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140808\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464617063\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022103177\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gaiiden\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n39 minutes ago, Gaiiden said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit was air park\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurrently abandoned but has been integrated into Hooligan Labs airship mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks a lot. I\u0027ve expected that it could lie in ruins.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222607964\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140808\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464617063\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022103177\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gaiiden\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n39 minutes ago, Gaiiden said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr schedule things better \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, I\u0027ve tried. But it\u0027s a pain even with 3 satellites in KSO and contracts expiring around every 6-12 hours, plus the desired spot being out of darkness on 3 / 3 basis. \u0022Schedule better\u0022 means \u0022don\u0027t fly or miss something\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s another possibility: try to revive the mod \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-30T14:43:40Z\u0022 title=\u002205/30/2016 02:43  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 30, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Ser\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Acvila","CreatedById":155891,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-30T14:49:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222607934\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140808\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464614817\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022104207\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ser\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Ser said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre you sure? Neither the description nor the video shows that this mod can freeze an aircraft mid-flight and let you switch to space center and back.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou are right, i didn\u0027t read well, it\u0027s only for time control and pause it, not switching vessels. there is a mod which allow you to launch a two stage ship and after decouple first stage u can go to orbit with second stage and after that you can go back time and land first stage, maybe that mod can do what u say, but i don\u0027t remember it\u0027s name.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ser","CreatedById":104207,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-30T14:52:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222608017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140808\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464619762\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155891\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Acvila\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Acvila said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou are right, i didn\u0027t read well, it\u0027s only for time control and pause it, not switching vessels. there is a mod which allow you to launch a two stage ship and after decouple first stage u can go to orbit with second stage and after that you can go back time and land first stage, maybe that mod can do what u say, but i don\u0027t remember it\u0027s name.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s FMRS mod. Last time I was using it, it was all around separating stages. But I need my plane in one piece. Thanks for the effort.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Acvila","CreatedById":155891,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-30T14:56:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyeah, FMRS. sorry i couldn\u0027t help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-30T15:32:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222608002\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140808\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464619102\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022104207\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ser\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n53 minutes ago, Ser said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks a lot. I\u0027ve expected that it could lie in ruins.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDunclaw appears to have recompiled it for 1.1.2, dll at this link: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/dunclaw/AirPark/blob/893c1263c942c8e24b11e2d47e13173448877533/GameData/AirPark/Plugins/AirPark.dll\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/dunclaw/AirPark/blob/893c1263c942c8e24b11e2d47e13173448877533/GameData/AirPark/Plugins/AirPark.dll\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ser","CreatedById":104207,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-30T15:51:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222608074\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140808\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464622323\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152460\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022swjr-swis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, swjr-swis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDunclaw appears to have recompiled it for 1.1.2, dll at this link: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/dunclaw/AirPark/blob/893c1263c942c8e24b11e2d47e13173448877533/GameData/AirPark/Plugins/AirPark.dll\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/dunclaw/AirPark/blob/893c1263c942c8e24b11e2d47e13173448877533/GameData/AirPark/Plugins/AirPark.dll\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAwesome\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}